Error: Error: "Unable To Allocate XMB Of RAM. Exiting."

Solution: 1. Log in to your Pterodactyl panel and navigate to your server.
2. Click on the "File Manager" tab and then open the "server.properties" file.
3. Locate the line that says "memory." It will look something like this: "memory=1024M."
4. Increase the amount of memory allocated to the server by changing this line to a higher value. For example,
